text: Zeleny Gai is an impact crater in Ukraine (Kirovohrad Oblast). It is 3.5 km (2.2 mi) in diameter and the age is estimated to be 80 Â± 20 million years (Upper Cretaceous). The crater is not exposed at the surface. == References == Category:Impact craters of Ukraine Category:Cretaceous impact craters Category:Geography of Kirovohrad Oblast
